The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has appointed a 5-member executive caretaker committee for the Rivers State chapter of the party. Lanre Issa-Onilu, APC National Publicity Secretary, announced this in a statement on Friday. The caretaker committee to oversee the Party’s affairs in the state will be chaired by Barr. Isaac Abott Ogbobula. Other members are: Mr. Friday Kinika Owhor, Mrs. Beatrice Amobi, Prince Abolo Stephen and Mr. Baridon Badom (Secretary). Meanwhile, the APC NWC has also approved the schedule of activities/timetable for the conduct of ward, local government and state cogresses in Rivers. The breakdown as follows: *Tuesday 17th September, 2019 – Ward Congresses *Wednesday 18th – Friday 20th September, 2019 – Appeals arising from Ward Congresses *Saturday 21st September, 2019 – LGA Congresses *Monday 23rd – Wednesday 25th September, 2019 – Appeals arising from State Congresses *Saturday 28th September, 2019 – State Congresses *Monday 30th September – Wednesday 2nd October, 2019 – Appeals arising from State Congresses. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.